ClickHouse/ClickHouse#44301.body:
```sql
create dictionary test_dict (id UInt64, val UInt64) PRIMARY KEY id LAYOUT(FLAT) SOURCE(CLICKHOUSE(QUERY 'SELECT number as id, number as val FROM numbers(100)')) LIFETIME (0);

create table test_table engine=Log AS SELECT * FROM numbers(200);
create table test_table_dist engine=Distributed('test_shard_localhost', currentDatabase(), test_table)  AS test_table;

SELECT number, dictGet('test_dict', 'val', toUInt64(number)) FROM test_table_dist;
```

gives exception

```
Code: 8. DB::Exception: Received from localhost:9000. DB::Exception: Cannot find column `dictGet('test_dict', 'val', toUInt64(number))` in source stream, there are only columns: [number, dictGet('default.test_dict', 'val', toUInt64(number))]. (THERE_IS_NO_COLUMN)
```

workaround is to add the db name to dictGet explicitly:

```sql
SELECT number, dictGet(currentDatabase() || '.test_dict', 'val', toUInt64(number)) FROM test_table_dist;
```

Related to https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse/pull/21859 and https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse/issues/21632

