ClickHouse/ClickHouse#101269.body:
### Describe the bug

Incorrect result when maxint is compared with bool.

Found by SQLancer

### How to reproduce

https://fiddle.clickhouse.com/53b130c5-841e-4a46-86a8-8269c87fdd9c

```
create table t (b Int8) ORDER BY ();
insert into t values (1), (0);

SELECT count() FROM t WHERE (2147483648 > b) AND 2147483648; -- BUG! returns 0

-- All this options return 2
SELECT count() FROM t WHERE 2147483648;
SELECT countIf((2147483648 > b) AND 2147483648) FROM t;
SELECT count() FROM t WHERE (2147483648 > b);
SELECT countIf((2147483648 > b)) FROM t;
```

### Error message and/or stacktrace

```
The optimizer converts AND 2147483648 by casting the integer to UInt8 via toUInt8, which truncates 2147483648 to 0 (since 2147483648 mod 256 = 0). This is a constant folding bug: when a large integer literal is used as a boolean predicate, the implicit conversion to UInt8 loses the truthiness.
```
